================================
things to do
================================

- simulation

  * tune geometry in "siegfried.gdml" according to technical drawing
  
  * use ROOT to check the geometry
  
  * tune the generator setup in "Tl208_top10cm.mac"
  
  * get familiar with the data structure in the output ROOT file
    (http://www.mppmu.mpg.de/~jingliu/cgi-bin/viewvc.cgi/doc/GERDAUsersGuide/)
    (chapter I/O scheme -> GEOutputCrystal)

  * select the DEP events. (single segment events, energy cut)
  
  * write a script (in MaGe/sandbox) to simulate the PS of DEP events

  * use the same way to create a background data sample (a gamma line)

- data

  * find out the data

  * select the DEP events

  * convert the selected events from Gerda format to Majorana format

  * do the same thing for a background data sample (a gamma line nearby)

- compare

  * learn how to use NN

  * train NN

  * create some distributions to compare
    
    o risetime
    
    o NN output

  * draw some conclusion

- memo

  * document every step

================================
how to use drawgdml.C
================================
$ root
root[] .x drawgdml.C("siegfried.gdml")


================================
how to tune generator
================================
$ MaGe Tl208_top10cm.mac
$ /remote/gx336-01/usr/wired3-14.2b4/bin/wired G4Data0.heprep


================================
how to use SVN (work with others)
================================

$ svn co file:///home/pclg-13/jingliu/svn/PSA  # get a copy
$ svn ci -m "what are the changes" changedFilesOrDirectories # commit your modification
$ svn st -vvv # check status
$ svn up  # update the current directory
